15 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable and distinguished
16 Georgian be recognized appropriately by dedicating an intersection in his memory.
17 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED AND ENACTED BY THE GENERAL
18 ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA that the intersection of State Route 400 and Whelchel
19 Road/Burnt Stand Road in Lumpkin County is dedicated as the Trooper First Class 2 Chase
20 W. Redner Memorial Intersection.
21 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Transportation is authorized and
22 directed to erect and maintain appropriate signs dedicating the Trooper First Class 2 Chase
23 W. Redner Memorial Intersection.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
25 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the family of
26 Trooper Chase Winston Redner and to the Department of Transportation.
